entries.femaleVariant: I saw Adam Smasher.
Got any jobs for me?
I saw him, Rogue. Adam Smasher.
Saw him where?
Here, in town. Yorinobu let him out of his cage when... when Hanako was kidnapped.
What did they expect would happen, our "unknown assailants?" Hm?
If I had to guess, they had good intentions when it came to Hanako, just that.. things must've spun a little out of control.
Why am I not surprised...? Know what I'd say to 'em, though? If I could talk to 'em, face to face?
That sooner or later, they'll get what's coming to 'em. Night City isn't what it used to be. That includes Arasaka.
And one of those "unknown assailants" isn't who he used to be, either. You think they'd understand?
Probably.
Rogue's also different.
Rogue isn't who she used to be, either.
I gotta go, V. Still a lotta biz that needs conductin'.
I'd say that was obvious.
Look out for yourself.
Who knows, probably. I'm sure they had their reasons.
I was wondering... wouldn't happen to have any gigs for me?
Nope.
Nothing...? Really?
Not for you.
Appreciate your honesty.
Are we cool?
Thanks. Appreciate your honesty.
Rogue – are we cool? 'Cause there are other fixers I can call...
Be my guest, if all you want are small-time smash-and-grabs.
Only thing you'll get here for free.
See the regulars? They've got dozens of jobs behind them. They trust each other.
Now put yourself in my shoes. How do you think it'll look when they found out I'm putting a crew together with you in it?
You had one job with Dex and fucked it up spectacularly.
You know that's not true.
Who cares? This isn't about skill, V. Only thing that matters is reputation.
Why do you think you work alone?
Fuck. Could've seen that coming. Arasaka's now looking for "unknown assailants." Again.
They had good intentions.
They had to... improvise.
Sounds like they ran out of options and had to think quick – improvise.
That op with Hellman worked out in the end.
That op with Hellman... worked out in the end.
I know.
Look, V. Just do what you do best, all right?
Cutting half o' Night City's power to down an AV...
That's how shit around here used to get done.
Panam deserves some credit.
How do things get done now?
How are things done now?
Conservatively. Everything's cold, calculated – less improvisation.
Sounds like you miss the good ol' days.
Heh. If you went back in time and told me I'd be a fixer, I'd've laughed in your face.
Can I ask you a personal question?
Sure. But ask at your own risk.
You knew Johnny Silverhand. What was he like?
How is it being the boss of the Afterlife?
Forget I said anything.
You used to know Johnny Silverhand. What was he like?
You know what... forget I said anything.
Strong, arrogant, uncompromising.
Can I ask you a personal question?
Probably for the best.
Johnny...?
Where did that come from?
He'd burn down half the city just to prove he was right.
And burn the other half just for fun.
He was like a kid with a box o' matches and a can of CHOOH2.
Easy to fall for, huh...?
Yeah...
Tough luck.
Anyway, doesn't matter. I won't speak ill of the dead.
How is it, being the boss of the Afterlife?
What is this, am I on News 54 Entertainment?
Seem to be as many rumors about him as there were fifty years ago. And not all of 'em gel together.
I know you two were close. That's why I asked.
Hmm... what was Johnny like...?
You don't know the half of it.
Panam deserves most of the credit. Wouldn't have happened without her.
I know. S'why I recommended her to you.
Is that all?
Anyway, I don't like that label – "boss." Makes it sound like I've got an army of greasy henchmen.
What would you rather go by?
Hmm. Good question. I'd have to think about that one...
You know what? I'll add it to my list of things to do, riiiight at the very bottom.
And was it worth it in the end?
For their sakes – I hope so.
See ya.
